title: For Sale:  S&W 38 Special CTG
location: Eden Prairie, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent: I am offering a very unusual weapon but not asking a "rare" price.  This is a Smith and Wesson 38 Special CTG.  Blued, 4 in barrel.  It is presented in the "Fitz Colt" style that was very popular with police officers in the old days as it allowed a very fast draw and quick shot.  (I do not know its age but could supply the serial number to a serious buyer and you can look it up.) The major noticeable attributes of a Fitz Colt are an open trigger guard and "hammerless".  This allowed the officer to use a holster with an open side so the finger is on the trigger as you are pulling it out.  First shot survives!  It fires well. Shoots both double and single action but single requires a half cock to get your thumb on the hammer.  (not really meant for single action)  Its a fun, unusual gun to the right guy.  Rubbber grips/pacmire style.  I will entertain any reasonable offer or trade.
